FT  03 AUG 94 / World Trade News: Japanese to move TV output to Mexico
Matsushita Television, a major unit of Matsushita Electric Industrial, will
shift production of colour televisions to a subsidiary in Mexico from
January 1995, Reuter reports from Tokyo.
The plant in Mexico, which has being making only television casings, will
make about 1.5m colour TVs a year. Matsushita Television will also move
engineering and administrative operations to a new site in southern
California, with operations set to begin by April 1995.
